  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Monitoring and protecting uMkhuze Game Reserve&#x2019;s black and white rhino populations in KwaZulu-Natal</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">award protect the indigenous black and white rhino populations in uMkhuze Game Reserve in KwaZulu Natal, South Africa.. By 2020, to increase MGR&#x2019;s black and white rhino populations to &gt;46 and &gt;20 respectively, such that they contribute to the targets of: the South African Biodiversity Management Plan for black rhino (gazetted into law on January 25, 2013) and the draft new white rhino conservation plan To manage uMkhuze Game Reserve&#x2019;s rhino populations for maximum growth; 2. To provide 24/7 protection for the black rhinos and other wildlife within the Reserve</narrative>
  </description>
